A manhunt has been launched after an inmate absconded from a Scottish prison. John Paul Lynch, 45, who is a prisoner at HMP Castle Huntly, was reported missing on Thursday evening. He is described as white, with brown hair, an average build and around 5’7 tall. Lynch also has a distinctive scar on the left side of his face. He was last seen in a cream jacket, blue jeans and black shoes and was cleanly shaved and wearing glasses. Lynch is originally from Paisley and police believe he may returned to the area. A Police Scotland spokesperson said: ‘Police are appealing for information to help trace 45-year-old John Paul Lynch, an inmate at HMP Castle Huntly, Dundee, who has absconded. ‘He was reported missing to police around 6.45 pm on Thursday, 3 March, 2022. ‘If seen, members of the public should contact Police Scotland on 101.’ Get in touch with our news team by emailing us at webnews@metro.co.uk. For more stories like this, check our news page.